@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>Kartverket users, we take your privacy seriously and are committed to protecting your personal data in accordance with GDPR.</p>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">What we collect</h2>
<ul class="list-disc ml-6">
    <li>Username, email, and password (encrypted) when you register an account.</li>
    <li>Geolocation data submitted with obstacles or during map interactions.</li>
    <li>Reports you submit, including descriptions, location, and ownership information.</li>
    <li>Information on who submitted each report and which department it belongs to.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Why we store data</h2>
<ul class="list-disc ml-6">
    <li>To manage accounts and authentication.</li>
    <li>To display, update, and share obstacle reports with relevant users.</li>
    <li>To improve application functionality and maintain security.</li>
    <li>For administrative purposes and legal compliance.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Data sharing</h2>
<ul class="list-disc ml-6">
    <li>Data is only shared with other registered users within the same department or with users explicitly granted access.</li>
    <li>We do not sell or distribute personal data to third parties.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Data retention</h2>
<p>
    If a user account is deleted, the associated reports and submissions are retained for record-keeping and auditing purposes.
    Personal identifiers may be removed where feasible, but some historical data is preserved to maintain integrity of the registry.
</p>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Security</h2>
<p>We implement industry-standard security measures, including encryption and access control, to protect your personal data against unauthorized access, loss, or misuse.</p>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Your rights</h2>
<ul class="list-disc ml-6">
    <li>You can request access to the personal data we store about you.</li>
    <li>You can request corrections, updates, or deletion of your personal data, subject to retention obligations.</li>
    <li>You can object to processing or request restriction of processing where applicable.</li>
    <li>For any inquiries regarding your personal data, you can contact our Data Protection Officer.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2">Contact</h2>
<p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@kartverket.no" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">privacy@kartverket.no</a>.</p>
